les, Lancashire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"Abt 1165–Abt. 1200":"about 1165–about 1200","1190–1248":"1190–1248","1165–1200":"1165–1200","1190":"1190","1248":"1248","1200":"1200","Abt 1165":"about 1165","1165":"1165","Abt. 1200":"about 1200","Eccles, Lancashire, England":"Eccles, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","Eccles, Barton upon Irwell, Lancashire, England":"Eccles, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Eccles","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Lancashire): habitational name from Eccles in Lancashire, or possibly from any of several other places so named in Kent, Norfolk, Berwickshire, and Dumfriesshire, from British <i>eglēs</i> ‘Romano-British Christian church’ (from Latin <i>ecclesia</i>, Greek <i>ekklēsia</i> ‘gathering, assembly’). Such places would have been the sites of notable pre-Anglo-Saxon churches or Christian places of communal worship."],"variants":[{"name":"Ackles","meanings":["Altered form of English   Eccles  ."]},{"name":"Exley","meanings":["English (Yorkshire): habitational name from Exley in Southowram (Yorkshire), from British <i>eglēs</i> ‘Romano-British Christian church’ (from Latin <i>ecclesia</i>, Greek <i>ekklēsia</i> ‘gathering, assembly’) + Old English <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’. Compare   Eccles  .","Americanized form of South German   Oechsle  ."]},{"name":"Echols","meanings":["Altered form of English   Eccles   and possibly also of German   Eckels  ."]},{"name":"Eckles","meanings":["English: variant of   Eccles  . This form is now rare in Britain."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Eccles was born about 1165, in Eccles, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter. He died about 1200, in his hometown, at the age of 37."},"et":{"Abt 1165–Abt. 1200":"umbes 1165–umbes 1200","1190–1248":"1190–1248","1165–1200":"1165–1200","1190":"1190","1248":"1248","1200":"1200","Abt 1165":"umbes 1165","1165":"1165","Abt. 1200":"umbes 1200","Eccles, Lancashire, England":"Eccles, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Eccles, Barton upon Irwell, Lancashire, England":"Eccles, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1165–Abt. 1200":"noin 1165–noin 1200","1190–1248":"1190–1248","1165–1200":"1165–1200","1190":"1190","1248":"1248","1200":"1200","Abt 1165":"noin 1165","1165":"1165","Abt. 1200":"noin 1200","Eccles, Lancashire, England":"Eccles, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Eccles, Barton upon Irwell, Lancashire, England":"Eccles, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1165–Abt. 1200":"environ 1165–environ 1200","1190–1248":"1190–1248","1165–1200":"1165–1200","1190":"1190","1248":"1248","1200":"1200","Abt 1165":"environ 1165","1165":"1165","Abt. 1200":"environ 1200","Eccles, Lancashire, England":"Eccles, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Eccles, Barton upon Irwell, Lancashire, England":"Eccles, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William Eccles est né environ 1165, à Eccles, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fille. Il est décédé environ 1200, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 37 ans."},"de":{"Abt 1165–Abt. 1200":"um 1165–um 1200","1190–